<meta name="description" content="Pawan Kumar Konda. He is an officer of the Indian Audit and Accounts Service of the 2010 batch, who is posted as Director of Audit in the Office of the Director General of Audit (Economic and Service Ministries), New Delhi. Pawan holds the national distinction of having qualified for JRF at the UGC-NET in 5 different subjects ­– History, Political Science, Public Administration, International & Area Studies and Sociology. In brief, he has achieved these distinctions of clearing 3 Public Service Examinations (2 APPSC and 1 UPSC), qualifying for JRF at UGC-NET for 5 subjects and completing 3 PG degrees in History, Political Science and Sociology, between the years 2003-04 to 2009-10. In addition to the above, in the arena of literary extra-curricular events, the author is the winner of 12 National Level Prizes, 17 State Level Prizes and 83 Inter-Collegiate/Inter-School Level Prizes in Elocution, Debate, Essay Writing and Quiz. The author is also the winner of the First Pro-Chancellor’s Gold Medal for the First Ranker in Bachelor of Arts at the 73rd Convocation of Andhra University, Visakhapatnam. Apart from this, he has been awarded the Comptroller and Auditor General’s Gold Medal for General Proficiency during training of 2010 batch of the Indian Audit and Accounts Service. 2000 Multiple Choice Questions On INDIAN POLITY. Aspirants of Civil Services Examination, State Civil Services Examinations, UGC National Eligibility Test, and any other Competitive Examinations containing the Indian Polity">
